humanMachineDialogue.author: Memory Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: According to the report, in the left axilla, sentinel lymph node #1 has metastatic breast carcinoma present in one of two lymph nodes examined (PART A). Additionally, in the left axilla, lymph node dissection shows metastatic breast carcinoma identified in 1 of 6 lymph nodes examined (PART C). Based on the AJCC staging system, this corresponds to N1 (metastases in 1 to 3 axillary lymph nodes).

humanMachineDialogue.author: ZS Reasoning
humanMachineDialogue.text: The report indicates that in the left axillary lymph node dissection, metastatic breast carcinoma was identified in 1 of 6 lymph nodes examined (part C). This corresponds to a pathologic N stage of N1.
